    <note type="biography">
        <p>Naval officer, hydrographer, and meteorologist. Commander of HMS <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi>, 1828–36. Tory MP for Durham, 1841–3. Governor of New Zealand, 1843–5. Superintendent of the dockyard at Woolwich, 1848–50. Chief of the meteorological department at the Board of Trade, 1854; chief of the Meteorological Office from 1855. Rear admiral, 1857; vice-admiral, 1863. FRS 1851.</p></note>
